args:
In the midst of preparing for the party,
a melancholy Nefaria muses about
her past. However, Saint Starfall must
wear a smile, so she cheers up and opts
to take on the treant that is commanding
the horde of fiends.
And the decoration for the Yuletree is a\nlittle something...like...this. Well?\nWhat do you think of it, darling?
Oh my goodness, a compliment from\nyou right in front of EVERYONE!\nWhat a sly one you are!
Er...right. Anyway, we should talk about\ntable settings. How's that going?
We've got forks and junk for everyone,\nas well as a huge pile of presents.
I'm amazed everything is running so\nsmoothly. I hope it continues until the\nnight of the big party.
Hey, boss! Mind if I pick yer brain for\na minute or three over here?
Xander and Elisanne are lookin' for ya.\nYeah, that's it. Anyway, uh...follow me!
All right. Can you take over here, Luca?
I can't believe that giant slab of bacon\nlured him away. Miracles never cease.\n...Okay, team huddle!
Hee hee! Oh, I'm such a naughty lady to\nbe keeping secrets from my darling.
But I mustâ€”for this secret will stoke the\nflames of our love to a roaring blaze!
Do you have a point, or are you just\nsaying things? 'Cause I'm busy.
I'm GETTING to it, Luca! Goodness!\n...Now then, Cleo? If you'd be so kind?
Not sure why this is suddenly my\nresponsibility...
Because you're the one who suggested it\nin the first place. Hurry, now! Chop chop!
All right, everyone, here's the deal...
I'd like for all of us to pitch in\non a gift for {player_name}.
To that end, we should discuss what\nsaid gift should be.
Why don't we just ask him what he wants?
Because that would ruin the surprise,\nyou feckless dunderhead!
Why do you think we had Ranzal lure him\naway so we could talk this over?
A surprise present?! Oh man, fun!\nLet's do this thing!
I'd like to give him something that truly\nexpresses how much we appreciate all\nthat he does for us.
Hey, yeah! Now I get it!
Man, I honestly had no idea Dragonyule\ncould be such a darn good time.
Think of how many years I've wasted\nnot celebrating it... Noooooo!

I appreciate your enthusiasm, but there
are a number of cultural challenges when
it comes to introducing people to a new
holiday.
You know, it's pretty crazy when you put\nit like that, Cleo.
This party's gonna bring all kinds of\npeople together, huh?
I mean, we've got tons of people from tons\nof different kingdoms here in the castle!
THERE you are! What's with the little\nvanishing act there, sister?
Say, you look glum, chum. What's up?
Merely that everyone's lively behavior is\ncausing me to bethink on days of yore.
Okay, not really sure what like half\nof those words mean.
As you know, I once ruled over a kingdom\nfar to the south.
We had a holiday similar to Dragonyule\nwhere baseborn and royalty alike would\nspend joyful times together.
However, my memories of it are befogged,\nand I find myself feeling quite alone.
Aw, Nefaria! Don't look so sad!
I mean, your old friends wouldn't want you\nto be SAD when you think about 'em.
Memories aren't for making us feel lonely\nand downâ€”they're for making us peppy\nand happy and generally awesome!
What are you two standing about for?\nFiends are on the attack, and our foe\nthis time is no laughing matter!
The treant leader of the fiends itself is\nat our very door!
Let us smite it, and give the people an\nevent to remember! Now, make great\nhaste and sally for... Hrm?
Your countenance is clouded, Nefaria.\nIs something amiss?
I cannot abide seeing Saint Starfall \nof all people make such a face.
Even saints feel low on occasion.
Well, I suppose that's technically true...
But such a thing ill suits both Saint Starfall\nand a monarch.
It was you who explained this truth\nof monarchy to me, was it not?\nFor are you not yourself a queen?
I may once have been so, yes.\n...Ah! Which means I am one still!
I see now! Even if my kingdom has fallen,\nthe memories of it live on in my bosom!
Heck yeah! ...I mean, coulda done without\nthe bosom part, but heck yeah anyway!
Thank you, Notte. And you as well, Xander.

Now let us be off to battle, that we may
celebrate a Dragonyule for the ages!
One which burns inside our memories
for time immemorial!
I have transcended time itself to become\nSaint Starfall, and this will be my mission!
